<ul><li>In a metallic conductor, some electrons are&nbsp;<b>delocalised</b>.</li><li>The&nbsp;<b>delocalised electrons</b>&nbsp;are the&nbsp;<b>charge carriers</b>&nbsp;in the metal.</li><li>When a voltage is applied across a the metal, the conduction electrons are&nbsp;<b>attracted towards the positive terminal</b>&nbsp;of the metal.</li></ul>